______________________________________________________________________
Amendment No. 1 to Senate Bill 153
Amend Senate Bill 153 as originally introduced:
Page 1, delete lines 10 and 11, and substitute the following:
"OF TITLE 24 OF THE ARKANSAS CODE; TO
AMEND THE LAW REGARDING THE PAYMENT OF
RETIREMENT BENEFITS TO VARIOUS CITY
OFFICIALS; AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES."
AND
Page 1, delete line 17, and substitute the following:
"CODE; AND TO AMEND THE LAW REGARDING THE
PAYMENT OF RETIREMENT BENEFITS TO VARIOUS
CITY OFFICIALS."
AND
Delete everything after the enacting clause, and substitute the following:
"SECTION 1. Arkansas Code § 24-12-120(c), concerning payment of
retirement benefits to city attorneys in cities of the first class and cities
of the second class, is amended to read as follows:
(c) All payments of retirement benefits under this section shall be
payable monthly and shall be paid from the general funds of by the city.
*.LJH268*
