SECTION 2. Arkansas Code § 24-12-121(b)(2), concerning retirement
payments to city clerks and clerk-treasurers, is amended to read as follows:
(2) The retirement pay shall be paid by the city from its
general fund account.
SECTION 3. Arkansas Code § 24-12-122(b)(2), concerning retirement
payments to deputy city clerks, is amended to read as follows:
(2) The retirement pay shall be paid by the city from its
general fund account when appropriated for that purpose by the governing body
of the city.
SECTION 4. Arkansas Code § 24-12-123(a)(2), concerning retirement
payments to mayors of cities of the first class, is amended to read as
follows:
(2) The retirement payments shall be paid monthly and shall be
paid from the city general fund by the city.
SECTION 5. Arkansas Code § 24-12-125(b)(2), concerning retirement
payments to treasurers of cities of the first class, is amended to read as
follows:
(2) Upon approval by the governing body of the city, the
retirement pay shall be paid by the city from its general fund account.
SECTION 6. Arkansas Code § 24-12-127(b)(2), concerning retirement
payments to recorder-treasurers and city treasurers of cities of the second
class, is amended to read as follows:
(2) The retirement pay shall be paid by the city from its
general fund account."
